Temperatures in the mid-60s, 53% humidity, and wind wilted the 8,000
runners in the 12th Old Style/Chicago marathon on Sunday, which began
at Daley Plaza and wound through flat city streets. Organizers insist
this race is world-class with the world's richest purse, although it
lost its sponsor in 1986, staged no race in 1987, and no drug testing
is done. Paul Davies-Hale of England won in 2:11:25, the slowest
winning time since 1982.  It was his first marathon. Lisa Weidenbach
of Washington won among the women in 2:28:15. Each won $50,000. Second
place winners got $30,000 and third place $20,000.  Wheelchair races
are included.</SUM>

<SUM
