On Sunday Ernesto Beatriz Martinez of Mexico City won the San Diego
International Marathon in 2:16:12. Marie Rollins won the women's race
in 2:39:05. They received $5,000 each. Second place took $2,500 and
third $1,500. The starting line was on East Mission Bay Drive. The
city doesn't allow vehicles on the course from miles 18-22.  There
were 3,056 entries for the full marathon and 2,958 for the
half. Jeffrey Holyfield won the men's half in 1:07:44, Katie Webb the
women's half in 1:21:46, Bill Fricke the wheelchair marathon in
1:55:30, and 14-year old Eric Neitzel the wheelchair half in
1:13:14.</SUM>

