Sunday's America's Finest City HomeFed Half Marathon is scheduled to
begin at 7am at the Cabrillo Monument atop the Point Loma
Peninsula. It will wind to a finish line in Balboa Park. The course is
considered to be challenging and difficult. Most elite runners who
train in San Diego stay away from the race. Some competitors have run
in the Trib 10K in May, the Coronado Half Marathon in July, the
Goodwill Games 10K last month in Seattle, Grandma's Marathon, the New
York City Marathon, the Twin Cities Marathon, the San Francisco
Marathon, the Nebraska Half Marathon, and marathons in Houston and
Boston.</SUM>

