Foreigners continued their domination of the New York City
Marathon. Sunday's race was plagued by heat and humidity, with the
temperature reaching 72 and humidity peaking at 66%. The hottest year
in this race's history was 1984 when the temperature reached
79. Douglas Wakiihuri, a Kenyan who trains in Japan, won overall in
2:12:39.  Poland's Wanda Panfil, who lives in Mexico, was the women's
winner in 2:30:45. The last American men's winner was Alberto Salazar
in 1982. The last American women's champion was Miki Gorman in
1977. Wakiihuri also won the 1989 London Marathon and the 1990
Commonwealth Games marathon.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d28"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="WSJ910326-0090"
SELECTOR="E"
