SUMMARIZER="H">  

Sites of potential marathon-centered vacations include Bangkok
(November), Belgrade (held despite Yugoslavia's turmoil), Berlin (Sept
27th, grown with the wall's demise), Bermuda, Brussels ($16 entry
fee), Budapest (offering a half-marathon and mini- marathon along the
Danube), Iceland, London (April 12th; the world's largest marathon,
with restricted entry but no qualifying times), Moscow, Munich
(repeating the 1972 Olympic route and finishing in the same stadium),
Paris, Portland (including a five-mile run, five-mile walk, and a kids
run), Rome, Seoul, Stockholm (May), Tel Aviv (passing houses hit by
Gulf War Scud missiles, with a half-marathon and fun run), Venice
($40), and Vienna.</SUM>

<SUM
