The Long Beach Marathon Sunday had its largest-ever field with 4,021
entrants. Rex Wilson of New Zealand won in 2:12:27 and Wen Yanmin of
China won in 2:43:33, each setting course records and winning
$9,500. Robert Molinatti of Huntington Beach won the wheelchair
division in 1:47:59. The Pacific Rim Marathon, of teams from invited
countries, was run within the marathon.  The men's and women's winners
shrewdly waited for others to make mistakes and the sun to take its
toll. Wilson wanted to run at a 5-minute pace so was forced to take
the lead at ten miles. He commented that he hated marathons.</SUM>
